<subSubSection id="C337088DF767B126B182F95B30F544D7" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F767B126B182F95B33134433" blockId="18.[151,1436,1554,1978]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F767B126B182F95B32C245F9" box="[199,251,1700,1726]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: In his original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F767B126B3FFF95C318A45FF" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[698,947,1699,1726]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 99)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that he had several specimens at hand,but only males[“ 
<emphasis id="B9598714F767B126B0EAF938312945A3" box="[431,784,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">Specimina nostra,masculina...</emphasis>
”(in plural)]. According to Sundevall’s acquisition catalogue, it seems there were 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF767B126B08AF91330454447" box="[463,636,1771,1798]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
available. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F767B126B3B9F91436224447" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[764,1051,1771,1797]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 22)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 659766 [6504] as a “type”, which we treat as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F767B126B366F8F030B6446B" box="[547,655,1807,1833]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F767B126B53EF8F03769446B" box="[1147,1360,1807,1833]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" value="1842-02-11">11 February 1842</date>
at the Apies River. The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F767B126B02BF8CC3035440F" box="[366,524,1843,1869]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539">paralectotype</typeStatus>
NRM 537999 [6505] is a mounted male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F767B126B53CF8CC3769440F" box="[1145,1360,1843,1869]" pageId="18" pageNumber="539" value="1842-02-17">17 February 1842</date>
at the Apies River.
</paragraph>
